  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering is complex and involves multiple levels of legislation and regulations:\n\n1. International Level\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Legal Elements\n- Criminal penalties for money laundering\n- Mandatory financial institution reporting\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture provisions\n- International cooperation mechanisms\n\n4. Enforcement Components\n- Financial crime investigation units\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Regulatory bodies\n- Treasury departments\n\n5. Compliance Requirements\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Customer due diligence\n- Risk assessment protocols\n- Reporting suspicious transactions\n\n6. Specific Prohibited Activities\n- Concealing financial sources\n- Converting illegal funds\n- Transferring illicit proceeds\n- Disguising money origins\n\nThe framework aims to detect, prevent, and prosecute financial crimes through comprehensive legal and regulatory strategies.",
